To trigger an github actions workflow syncing to efs at /mnt/efs location on bastion host

curl -X POST \
  -H "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <GITHUB_TOKEN>" \
  https://api.github.com/repos/quilrbusiness/content-management-service/actions/workflows/aws-prod-eastus-efs-sync.yaml/dispatches \
  -d '{"ref":"aws-prod-eastus-efs-sync", "inputs":{"force_deploy":"templating"}}'
  
under force-deploy use - 'Comma-separated list of services to deploy manually'

example as below:


curl -X POST \
  -H "Accept: application/vnd.github+json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <GITHUB_TOKEN>" \
  https://api.github.com/repos/quilrbusiness/content-management-service/actions/workflows/aws-prod-apsouth-efs-sync.yaml/dispatches \
  -d '{"ref":"main", "inputs":{"force_deploy":"browser,classification,content_lambda,content_repo,dashboard,data_config,data_explorer,data_fabric,grouping,playbook,snowflake,templating"}}'
